`copy` requests an independent value.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    items ~= {"a", "b"}
    independent_items ~= copy items

    ~items.push("c") catch:
    ;

    io.line([: original length: [items.length()]])
    io.line([: copied length: [independent_items.length()]])
]

### Contract

- Source code does not silently copy an existing value when another name is created.
- When a value is copyable and an independent value is required, write `copy`.
- The copied value keeps the same semantic type.
- The receiving binding chooses its own mutability.
- Copying is separate from ownership transfer and separate from exclusive access.

Expressions that construct a new result from existing inputs are not implicit
copies of one input.

[codeblock, $code("bst"):
    total = left + right
    label = [: [first_name] [last_name]]
]

Those expressions create new result values through their own language rules.
